{{Infobox language |name=Bambassi |altname=Mao of Bambassi |nativename=Mao of Didessa |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region=in [[Benishangul-Gumuz Region]], east of [[Asosa]] |speakers=2,300 |date=2011 |ref=<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/myf|title=Màwés Aasʼè|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en}}</ref> |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic languages|Omotic]] |fam3=[[Mao languages|Mao]] |iso3=myf |glotto=bamb1262 |glottorefname=Bambassi }}
'''Bambassi''' is an [[Omotic]] [[Afroasiatic languages|Afroasiatic]] [[language]] spoken in [[Ethiopia]] around the towns of [[Bambasi]] and Didessa in the area east of [[Asosa]] in [[Benishangul-Gumuz Region]].<ref name=e18>{{Ethnologue18|myf}}</ref> The parent language group is the [[Mao languages|East Mao group]]. Alternative names for the language are Bambeshi, Siggoyo, Amam, Fadiro, Northern Mao, Didessa and Kere.
The most current information on the number of Bambassi speakers is not known, as the 2007 census grouped the Mao languages together, despite low lexical similarity. 33,683 mother tongue speakers of Maogna (covering Bambassi, [[Hozo language|Hozo]] and [[Seze language|Seze]]) were listed.<ref>[http://www.csa.gov.et/images/documents/pdf_files/regional/CountryLevel.pdf Ethiopia 2007 Census]</ref>
__NOTOC__
== Similarities == Bambassi has a 31% [[lexicon|lexical]] similarity with other Omotic languages.
== Phonology == Bambassi has 5 vowels: /a, e, i, o, u/. The vowels have lengthened forms, and Bambassi has contrastive vowel length.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Michael|first=Ahland,|date=2012|title=A Grammar of Northern Mao (Màwés Aas'è)|url=https://scholarsbank.uoregon.edu/xmlui/handle/1794/12456|journal=UO Libraries|language=en-US|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |+Consonants ! colspan="2" rowspan="2" | ! colspan="2" |[[Bilabial consonant|Bilabial]] ! colspan="2" |[[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ! rowspan="2" |[[Postalveolar consonant|Postalveolar]] ! rowspan="2" |[[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] ! colspan="2" |[[Velar consonant|Velar]] ! rowspan="2" |[[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- !<small>plain</small> ![[Ejective consonant|<small>ejective</small>]] !<small>plain</small> ![[Ejective consonant|<small>ejective</small>]] !<small>plain</small> ![[Ejective consonant|<small>ejective</small>]] |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Stop consonant|Stop]] !<small>voiceless</small> |p |pʼ |t |tʼ | | |k |kʼ | |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] |b | |d | | | |g | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Affricate consonant|Affricate]] | | | |t͡sʼ |(t͡ʃ) | | | | |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Fricative consonant|Fricative]] !<small>voiceless</small> | | |s | |ʃ | | | |h |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] | | |z | | | | | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] |m | |n | | | |ŋ | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Approximant consonant|Approximant]] | | |l | | |j |w | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Flap consonant|Flap]] | | |ɾ | | | | | | |}
