'''[[Cannabis]] in [[Bermuda]]''' is legal for medical use and decriminalized for recreational use.

==Medical use==
In November 2016, the Supreme Court of Bermuda ruled in favor of allowing the medical use of cannabis.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bell |first1=Jonathan |title=People can apply for medical cannabis |url=http://www.royalgazette.com/news/article/20161125/people-can-apply-for-medical-cannabis |accessdate=27 October 2018 |work=The Royal Gazette |date=November 25, 2016}}</ref>  As of July 2018, two doctors have been licensed to prescribe the drug.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bell |first1=Jonathan |title=Weeks: we need to talk about cannabis |url=http://www.royalgazette.com/politics/article/20180725/weeks-we-need-to-talk-about-cannabis |accessdate=27 October 2018 |work=The Royal Gazette |date=July 25, 2018}}</ref>

==Decriminalization==
In December 2017, Bermuda passed legislation decriminalizing personal possession of 7 grams or less of cannabis.<ref>[http://www.royalgazette.com/news/article/20171213/cannabis-decriminalisation-backed-in-senate Cannabis decriminalisation backed in Senate | The Royal Gazette:Bermuda News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.royalgazette.com/politics/article/20171209/house-cannabis-decriminalisation-passes House: cannabis decriminalisation passes | The Royal Gazette:Bermuda Politics<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

